The value sum[i+1][j+1][0] and sum[i+1][j+1][1] represents the number of Xs and Ys in grid[i][j] to grid[m-1][n-1]. When grid[i][j]=. Then sum[i+1][j+1][0]=sum[i][j+1][0] and sum[i+1][j+1][1]=sum[i][j+1][1].
When grid[i][j]='X' or 'Y', Then sum[i+1][j+1][0]=sum[i][j+1][0]+1 or sum[i+1][j+1][1]=sum[i][j+1][1]+1.
The value sum[i+1][j+1][0]==sum[i+1][j+1][1] represents that grid[i][j] to grid[m-1][n-1] contain Xs and Ys in the same number.
When sum[i+1][j+1][0]==sum[i+1][j+1][1] is true and sum[i+1][j+1][grid[i][j]&1]>=1, Then means that grid[0][0] to grid[i][j] is contained in the sub-matrix with the same number of Xs and Ys.

Therefore, sum[i][j][0] is not required, and the sum[i][j][1] can be merged into the two-dimensional array.

